---

## 1. Schema Design — ⭐⭐⭐⭐

### ✅ What's Well Done
- **GateEntry** model is comprehensive: `IN/OUT` enum, `isLateEntry` flag, `lateMinutes`, `linkedLeaveId`, policy snapshot reference
- **GatePass** model covers visitor tracking with approver audit trail
- **Violation** model has full escalation state machine (`NONE → WARNED → ESCALATED → RESOLVED`)
- **PolicySnapshot** captures policy state at the time of each gate event (audit-proof)
- **BuildingPolicy** has curfew settings, tolerance, notification controls, and violation windows
- Good use of indexes on `studentId`, `timestamp`, `isLateEntry`, `type`

### 🟡 Gaps

| Gap | Severity | Description |
|---|:---:|---|
| **No Attendance model** | 🔴 Critical | There is no dedicated `Attendance` or `DailyAttendance` model. Attendance is inferred indirectly from gate IN/OUT logs, which is unreliable |
| **No roll-call / headcount** | 🔴 Critical | No model for daily roll-call, night check, or hostel-presence tracking |
| **No `inCampus` status** | 🟠 Major | No real-time student presence tracking (in-hostel vs. out) |
| **Missing `GateEntry.direction` validation** | 🟡 Minor | No enforcement that OUT must be followed by IN (double OUT possible) |

---

## 2. Gate Entry/Exit Backend — ⭐⭐⭐⭐

### ✅ What's Well Done
- [createEntry()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/gate/gate.service.ts#33-226) is robust: student verification, hostel resolution via bed assignment, policy snapshot creation, late/overstay detection, violation creation with escalation — all in a single transaction
- Notification hooks for parent notification on entry/exit/late events
- Stats endpoint tracks today's in/out/late entries and pass statuses
- [findEntries()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/gate/gate.controller.ts#58-62) supports pagination and filtering by studentId, type, date range

### 🟡 Gaps

| Gap | Severity | Description |
|---|:---:|---|
| **No auto gate-pass linking** | 🟠 Major | Gate entry doesn't auto-validate against active gate passes |
| **No QR/NFC scan integration** | 🟠 Major | `gateNo` is manual text input — no barcode/QR/NFC endpoint |
| **No sequential entry validation** | 🟠 Major | System allows OUT → OUT or IN → IN without checking last state |
| **No real-time presence dashboard** | 🔴 Critical | No endpoint to show "who is currently in hostel" |
| **Leave auto-link missing** | 🟡 Minor | `linkedLeaveId` is optional and manual — should auto-detect active approved leave |
| **No bulk entry** | 🟡 Minor | No batch scan endpoint for security guards processing a queue |

---

## 3. Violations & Escalation — ⭐⭐⭐⭐

### ✅ What's Well Done
- [detectLateEntry()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/violations/violations.service.ts#72-97) correctly compares timestamp against curfew + tolerance
- [detectOverstay()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/violations/violations.service.ts#98-119) handles leave-linked overstay detection
- [evaluateEscalation()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/violations/violations.service.ts#142-150) escalation state machine based on repeated count within violation window
- Policy snapshot ensures violations are evaluated against the policy that was active at the time
- [getRepeatedCount()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/violations/violations.service.ts#124-141) uses a rolling window of days for escalation threshold
- [resolve()](file:///d:/Apps/hostel/BMS_hostel/apps/api/src/violations/violations.controller.ts#110-118) flow with resolver audit trail

### 🟡 Gaps

| Gap | Severity | Description |
|---|:---:|---|
| **No SMS/WhatsApp escalation** | 🟠 Major | Violation notifications are stub/IN_APP only — no parent/warden WhatsApp alerts |
| **No early-exit detection** | 🟡 Minor | `EARLY_EXIT` enum exists but no detection logic in gate service |
| **No repeat violation reporting** | 🟡 Minor | No API endpoint for "students with most violations in X days" |

---

## 4. Leave ↔ Gate Integration — ⭐⭐⭐

### ✅ What's Well Done
- Gate entries can be linked to leave requests via `linkedLeaveId`
- Overstay detection uses leave's `toDate` for violation calculation
- Leave policy (`maxLeaveDays`) enforced from building policy

### 🟠 Gaps

| Gap | Severity | Description |
|---|:---:|---|
| **No auto gate-pass on leave approval** | 🔴 Critical | When leave is `WARDEN_APPROVED`, no gate pass is auto-created — student needs a separate pass manually |
| **No gate-based leave verification** | 🟠 Major | Gate OUT entry should verify student has approved leave for that date range |
| **No return check-in flow** | 🟠 Major | When student returns from leave (gate IN), leave status should auto-close/complete |
| **No attendance impact tracking** | 🟠 Major | No tracking of how leave affects daily attendance records |

---

## 5. Attendance Tracking — ⭐⭐ (CRITICAL GAP)

> [!CAUTION]
> This is the biggest gap in the system. There is **NO dedicated attendance tracking**.

### 🔴 What's Missing Entirely

| Feature | Enterprise Expectation | Current State |
|---|---|---|
| **Daily attendance record** | Computed from gate IN/OUT entries per student per day | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Night roll-call** | Warden marks present/absent at night | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Attendance percentage** | Running % for each student (required for 75% rule) | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Mess attendance** | Breakfast/lunch/dinner tracking | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Attendance reports** | Monthly/semester-wise reports, exportable | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Attendance dashboard** | Real-time who's in/out with counts per hostel/floor | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Student presence status** | Live `IN_HOSTEL` / `OUT_ON_LEAVE` / `OUT_WITHOUT_LEAVE` | ❌ Not implemented |
| **Auto-absent marking** | Students not scanned IN by curfew auto-marked absent | ❌ Not implemented |

