## 6. Frontend UI — ⭐⭐⭐

### ✅ What's Well Done
- Gate page exists (353 lines) with tabbed UI: Entries tab + Passes tab
- Violation page (232 lines) with filtering by type/escalation state and resolve flow
- Both pages use shared UI components (Card, Badge, Modal, Pagination)

### 🟠 Gaps

| Gap | Severity | Description |
|---|:---:|---|
| **No attendance dashboard** | 🔴 Critical | No dedicated attendance page showing daily present/absent view |
| **No real-time presence board** | 🔴 Critical | No live view showing "128/145 students currently in hostel" |
| **No student self-view** | 🟠 Major | Students can't see their own gate history or attendance % |
| **No calendar view** | 🟠 Major | No month-view showing leave days, present days, absent days |
| **Gate page lacks quick-scan UX** | 🟠 Major | No streamlined scan interface for security guards (type USN → auto IN/OUT) |

---

## 7. Reporting & Analytics — ⭐⭐

### ✅ What's Well Done
- Basic stats endpoint (today's entries/exits/late entries, active/used passes)
- Violation stats (counts by type, escalation, today/total)

### 🔴 What's Missing

| Feature | Enterprise Expectation |
|---|---|
| **Attendance percentage API** | Per student, per hostel, per floor, with date range filters |
| **Absence report** | "Students absent for 3+ consecutive nights" |
| **Leave utilization report** | Days of leave used vs. policy limit per student |
| **Violation trends** | Weekly/monthly charts of violations by type, hostel, student |
| **Exportable reports** | CSV/PDF export for admin/warden reports |
| **Parent report access** | Parents viewing their ward's attendance/violations |

