## 🏆 Enterprise-Grade Recommendation Priority

### P0 — Must Have (Critical for "Attendance Management")

| # | Item | Effort |
|---|---|:---:|
| 1 | **DailyAttendance model** — computed from gate entries, stores PRESENT/ABSENT/ON_LEAVE per student per day | M |
| 2 | **Real-time presence tracking** — `studentPresenceStatus` enum on User or BedAssignment (`IN_HOSTEL`, `OUT`, `ON_LEAVE`) updated on each gate IN/OUT | M |
| 3 | **Attendance dashboard page** — live presence count, daily summary table, student-level drill-down | L |
| 4 | **Auto gate-pass on leave approval** — WARDEN_APPROVED triggers gate pass creation for the leave dates | S |
| 5 | **Sequential IN/OUT enforcement** — prevent duplicate IN or OUT without opposite | S |

### P1 — Should Have (Enterprise Quality)

| # | Item | Effort |
|---|---|:---:|
| 6 | **Night roll-call feature** — warden marks present/absent batch, creates DailyAttendance records | M |
| 7 | **Attendance percentage API** — rolling calculation with leave deductions, 75% rule check | M |
| 8 | **Student self-view** — "My Attendance" page with calendar view, gate history, violation history | M |
| 9 | **Auto leave-link on gate OUT** — if student has approved leave for today, auto-link the gate entry | S |
| 10 | **WhatsApp violation alerts** — send violation notification to parent via WhatsApp (reuse existing service) | S |

### P2 — Nice to Have (Studio-Grade Polish)

| # | Item | Effort |
|---|---|:---:|
| 11 | **Quick-scan security UX** — streamlined gate UI: type USN → auto-detect IN/OUT → one-click log | M |
| 12 | **Attendance reports with export** — monthly/semester PDF/CSV reports | M |
| 13 | **Parent attendance view** — parent sees ward's attendance %, recent gate activity | S |
| 14 | **Mess attendance** — separate check-in for breakfast/lunch/dinner | L |
| 15 | **QR code scanning** — generate student QR codes for rapid gate scanning | M |

> **Effort Key:** S = Small (1-2 hours), M = Medium (3-6 hours), L = Large (8+ hours)

---

## 🏗️ Recommended Schema Additions

```prisma
model DailyAttendance {
  id         String   @id @default(uuid()) @db.Uuid
  studentId  String   @map("student_id") @db.Uuid
  date       DateTime @db.Date
  status     AttendanceStatus @default(UNKNOWN)
  firstIn    DateTime? @map("first_in")
  lastOut    DateTime? @map("last_out")
  lastIn     DateTime? @map("last_in")
  isOnLeave  Boolean  @default(false) @map("is_on_leave")
  leaveId    String?  @map("leave_id") @db.Uuid
  markedBy   String?  @map("marked_by") @db.Uuid  // warden for roll-call
  notes      String?  @db.Text

  @@unique([studentId, date])
  @@index([date])
  @@index([status])
  @@map("daily_attendance")
}

enum AttendanceStatus {
  PRESENT
  ABSENT
  ON_LEAVE
  LATE
  UNKNOWN  // not yet determined for today
}
```

---

## ✅ Bottom Line

The **gate entry/exit engine** and **violations/escalation system** are solidly built at near enterprise-grade level. The critical gap is the **absence of a dedicated attendance tracking layer** — the system logs gates but doesn't derive attendance from them. Adding a `DailyAttendance` model, real-time presence tracking, and an attendance dashboard would elevate this from 3.1/5 to 4.5/5 enterprise readiness.
